    solution: "Exactly 3 heads in 1000 fair coin flips is the most surprising because the expected number of heads is about 500. Getting only 3 is wildly far from that expectation.",
    lesson: "Surprise in probability often comes from distance from what the model expects, scaled by sample size. A fair coin expects about half heads.\n\nIn 10 flips, counts can wobble quite a bit. In 1000 flips, landing only 3 heads would be extraordinary, like the coin sending a tiny dramatic resignation letter.",
